about.summary: With dbt, data analysts and engineers can build analytics the way engineers build applications.

name: dbt
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "dbt" %}
{% set version = "0.21.0" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  - url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 078598ea2bea848db323676c9ee16c4535584d87babdbe91c2a149bb235f401e
    folder: dbt
  - url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}-core/{{ name }}-core-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 74626c1e32acfc3f49112b77029dac8dd6902c13dbfee184e74e659fe28ce51b
    folder: dbt-core
  - url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}-postgres/{{ name }}-postgres-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 00ccad11fce3e4d43f7e86c39b3e813924153189ed8288e9a721b20b3dc822a8
    folder: dbt-postgres
  - url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}-redshift/{{ name }}-redshift-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 79c29f0c032741fdfeffb23f9388ebf659c9b82aa70b228886d79e763bdbecf2
    folder: dbt-redshift
  - url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}-bigquery/{{ name }}-bigquery-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: d17e88d4b3534a5808ffefd1954c69df3ce93e4ac9b87219691ebeb384b349d3
    folder: dbt-bigquery
  - url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}-snowflake/{{ name }}-snowflake-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: f635463bcfa276ac34d9603f2808daa3c3a44bb1f36209efff9cf35111d0014e
    folder: dbt-snowflake

build:
  number: 2
  noarch: python

outputs:
  - name: dbt
    build:
      noarch: python
      script: python -m pip install --no-deps -vv ./dbt
    requirements:
      host:
        - pip
        - python >=3.6
      run:
        - python >=3.6
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-bigquery", exact=True) }}
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-core", exact=True) }}
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-postgres", exact=True) }}
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-redshift", exact=True) }}
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-snowflake", exact=True) }}

    test:
      imports:
        - dbt
      commands:
        - pip check
      requires:
        - pip


  - name: dbt-core
    build:
      noarch: python
      entry_points:
        - dbt = dbt.main:main
      script: python -m pip install --no-deps  -vv ./dbt-core

    requirements:
      host:
        - pip
        - python >=3.6
      run:
        - python >=3.6
        # https://github.com/dbt-labs/dbt-core/blob/v0.21.0/core/setup.py
        - jinja2 ==2.11.3
        - pyyaml >=3.11
        - agate >=1.6,<1.6.2
        - colorama >=0.3.9,<0.4.5
        - dataclasses >=0.6,<0.9
        - hologram ==0.0.14
        - isodate >=0.6,<0.7
        - json-rpc >=1.12,<2
        - logbook >=1.5,<1.6
        - mashumaro ==2.5
        - minimal-snowplow-tracker ==0.0.2
        - networkx >=2.3,<3
        - packaging ~=20.9
        - sqlparse >=0.2.3,<0.5
        - dbt-extractor ==0.4.0
        - typing-extensions >=3.7.4,<3.11
        - werkzeug >=1,<3

        # According to setup.py, "the following are all to match snowflake-connector-python"
        # - requests <3.0.0
        # - idna >=2.5,<4
        # - cffi >=1.9,<2.0.0

    test:
      imports:
        - dbt
        - dbt.adapters
      commands:
        - pip check
        - dbt --help
      requires:
        - pip


  - name: dbt-postgres
    build:
      noarch: python
      script: python -m pip install --no-deps -vv ./dbt-postgres

    requirements:
      host:
        - pip
        - python >=3.6
      run:
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-core", exact=True) }}
        - psycopg2-binary ~=2.8
        - python >=3.6

    test:
      imports:
        - dbt
        - dbt.adapters
      commands:
        - pip check
      requires:
        - pip


  - name: dbt-redshift
    build:
      noarch: python
      script: python -m pip install --no-deps -vv ./dbt-redshift

    requirements:
      host:
        - pip
        - python >=3.6
      run:
        - python >=3.6
        - boto3 >=1.4.4,<2.0.0
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-core", exact=True) }}
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-postgres", exact=True) }}

    test:
      imports:
        - dbt
        - dbt.adapters
      commands:
        - pip check
      requires:
        - pip

  - name: dbt-bigquery
    build:
      noarch: python
      script: python -m pip install --no-deps -vv ./dbt-bigquery

    requirements:
      host:
        - pip
        - python >=3.6
      run:
        - python >=3.6
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-core", exact=True) }}
        - google-api-core >=1.16.0,<2
        - google-cloud-bigquery >=1.25.0,<3
        - google-cloud-core >=1.3.0,<2
        - googleapis-common-protos >=1.6.0,<2
        - protobuf >=3.13.0,<4
        - six >=1.14.0

    test:
      imports:
        - dbt
        - dbt.adapters
      commands:
        - pip check
      requires:
        - pip

  - name: dbt-snowflake
    build:
      noarch: python
      script: python -m pip install --no-deps -vv ./dbt-snowflake

    requirements:
      host:
        - pip
        - python >=3.6
      run:
        - cryptography >=3.2,<4
        - {{ pin_subpackage("dbt-core", exact=True) }}
        - python >=3.6
        - requests <3.0.0
        - snowflake-connector-python>=2.4.1,<2.6.0

    test:
      imports:
        - dbt
        - dbt.adapters
      commands:
        - pip check
      requires:
        - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/dbt-labs/dbt
  summary: With dbt, data analysts and engineers can build analytics the way engineers build applications.
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: License.md

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - drewbanin
    - jthandy
    - maresb
    - thewchan
